<seg id=1> Fujian To Promote Fujian-Taiwan Trade And Economic Cooperation This Year </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Fuzhou, Jan. 10 (Xu Ting reporting): Fujian has made a proposal to put great effort into promoting trade and economic ties with Taiwan this year, expanding efforts to attract business from the island, and strengthening links with big enterprises and financial groups there. These efforts are to procure a range of investment from Taiwan into large projects, and to work hard at developing cooperation in the areas of trade and fisheries labor. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The relevant departments in Fujian province recently drafted up new measures to speed up the development of foreign trade and business in the province. These include the deepening of reforms for foreign trade and business, maintaining stable growth in exports, and continuing to expand the use of foreign investment, all of which make up the important parts of the province's work in foreign trade and investment for 1998. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Fujian is one of the fastest developing foreign business and trade areas in China's coastal region. </seg>
<seg id=5> The province's imports and exports totaled almost 20 billion U.S. dollars last year, and use of foreign investment surpassed 4 billion dollars. Projects using foreign contractors and labor reached 355 million U.S. dollars. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> According to reports, the main points of these new measures are to increase the scale of business, to form enterprise groups, to promote the reconstruction of the strategic nature of provincially-owned foreign trade companies, to strengthen product exports of pillar enterprises, and to organize the "Conference on the Promotion of Foreign Investment" and the "China Investment and Trade Talks Conference for 1998", both of which will take place in Hong Kong. </seg>
</p>
